sentences: Jessica Ruth Mueller (born February 20, 1983) is an American actress and singer.
She started her acting career in Chicago and won two Joseph Jefferson Awards in 2008 and 2011 for her roles as Carrie Pipperidge in Carousel and Amalia Balash in She Loves Me.
In 2011, she moved to New York City to star in a Broadway revival of musical On a Clear Day
In 2011, she moved to New York City to star in a Broadway revival of musical On a Clear Day
She won the 2014 Tony Award for Best Actress in a Leading Role in a Musical for her performance as Carole King in Beautiful: The Carole King Musical.
She went on to receive two additional Best Actress in a Musical Tony Award nominations for her leading roles in Waitress (2016) and the Broadway revival of Carousel (2018).
She went on to receive two additional Best Actress in a Musical Tony Award nominations for her leading roles in Waitress (2016) and the Broadway revival of Carousel (2018).
As of 2019, three of the four Mueller siblings had appeared in Broadway productions.
